<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-02-27T18:40:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-02-27T18:40:00-05:00" n="884" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d884">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/6408.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at Nuevo
                                    Laredo</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Nuevo Laredo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-02-27T17:00:00-06:40">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 27, 1913—5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>A peace commission will meet in Nuevo Laredo this evening, composed of
                            the following persons: Lieut. Manuel Carea Aldape, Delio Marcus Canton,
                            Perrajon Lupez, José M. Garza, Ramon and Ricardo Garcia Granados,
                            representing the States of Sonora, Chihuahua, Nuevo Leon, Coahuila, and
                            Tamaulipas. The object of the meeting is to agree on a basis for
                            permanent peace for Mexico.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Garrett</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>